<% content_for(:title) { "Cookie Policy - X-ROR" } %>
<% content_for(:seo_description) { "X-ROR Cookie Policy. Learn about the cookies we use, why we use them, and how to manage your cookie preferences." } %>
<%= render "shared/navbar" %>
<main class="flex-1 pb-16">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 pt-16 sm:px-6">
    <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Last updated: March 12, 2026</p>

    <h1 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight">Cookie Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
      This Cookie Policy explains what cookies are, how X-ROR ("we," "us," or "our") uses them
      on <strong>x-ror.fun</strong>, and how you can manage your preferences.
    </p>

    <!-- 1. What Are Cookies -->
    <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-bold">1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">
      Cookies are small text files placed on your device when you visit a website. They help the
      site remember your preferences, keep you logged in, and understand how you use the service.
      Cookies can be "session" cookies (deleted when you close your browser) or "persistent" cookies
      (remain on your device for a set period).
    </p>

    <!-- 2. How We Use Cookies -->
    <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-bold">2. How We Use Cookies</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">We use the following categories of cookies:</p>

    <h3 class="mt-6 text-lg font-semibold">2.1 Strictly Necessary Cookies</h3>
    <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">
      These cookies are essential for the Service to function. They enable core features like
      authentication and security. You cannot opt out of these cookies.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-3 overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm text-muted-foreground">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-border">
            <th class="py-2 pr-4 text-left font-semibold">Cookie Name</th>
            <th class="py-2 pr-4 text-left font-semibold">Purpose</th>
            <th class="py-2 pr-4 text-left font-semibold">Duration</th>
            <th class="py-2 text-left font-semibold">Provider</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-border/50">
            <td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="text-xs">_session_id</code></td>
            <td class="py-2 pr-4">Maintains your authenticated session</td>
            <td class="py-2 pr-4">Session</td>
            <td class="py-2">X-ROR</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-border/50">
            <td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="text-xs">_csrf_token</code></td>
            <td class="py-2 pr-4">Protects against cross-site request forgery attacks</td>
            <td class="py-2 pr-4">Session</td>
            <td class="py-2">X-ROR</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h3 class="mt-6 text-lg font-semibold">2.2 Functional Cookies</h3>
    <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">
      These cookies remember your choices and preferences to provide a more personalized experience.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-3 overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm text-muted-foreground">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-border">
            <th class="py-2 pr-4 text-left font-semibold">Cookie Name</th>
            <th class="py-2 pr-4 text-left font-semibold">Purpose</th>
            <th class="py-2 pr-4 text-left font-semibold">Duration</th>
            <th class="py-2 text-left font-semibold">Provider</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-border/50">
            <td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="text-xs">theme</code></td>
            <td class="py-2 pr-4">Remembers your dark/light mode preference</td>
            <td class="py-2 pr-4">1 year</td>
            <td class="py-2">X-ROR</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-border/50">
            <td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="text-xs">cookie_consent</code></td>
            <td class="py-2 pr-4">Stores your cookie consent preferences</td>
            <td class="py-2 pr-4">1 year</td>
            <td class="py-2">X-ROR</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h3 class="mt-6 text-lg font-semibold">2.3 Analytics Cookies</h3>
    <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">
      These cookies help us understand how visitors interact with our Service by collecting
      information anonymously. They are only set with your consent.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-3 overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm text-muted-foreground">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-border">
            <th class="py-2 pr-4 text-left font-semibold">Cookie Name</th>
            <th class="py-2 pr-4 text-left font-semibold">Purpose</th>
            <th class="py-2 pr-4 text-left font-semibold">Duration</th>
            <th class="py-2 text-left font-semibold">Provider</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-border/50">
            <td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="text-xs">[ANALYTICS_COOKIE_NAME]</code></td>
            <td class="py-2 pr-4">[Purpose of analytics cookie]</td>
            <td class="py-2 pr-4">[Duration]</td>
            <td class="py-2">[Analytics Provider]</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground italic">
      Update this table when you add an analytics service (e.g., Google Analytics, Plausible, etc.).
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-6 text-lg font-semibold">2.4 Marketing/Advertising Cookies</h3>
    <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">
      We currently do not use marketing or advertising cookies. If this changes in the future,
      we will update this policy and request your consent before setting such cookies.
    </p>

    <!-- 3. GDPR Consent -->
    <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-bold">3. Cookie Consent (GDPR)</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">
      Under the GDPR and ePrivacy Directive, we are required to obtain your consent before placing
      non-essential cookies on your device. When you first visit X-ROR, you will be presented with
      a cookie consent banner where you can accept or reject non-essential cookies. You can change
      your preferences at any time.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">
      Strictly necessary cookies do not require consent as they are essential for the Service to function.
    </p>

    <!-- 4. Managing Cookies -->
    <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-bold">4. How to Manage Cookies</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">You can control cookies in several ways:</p>
    <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
      <li><strong>Cookie consent banner:</strong> use our on-site cookie preferences to accept or reject non-essential cookies.</li>
      <li><strong>Browser settings:</strong> most browsers allow you to block or delete cookies. Check your browser's help documentation for instructions.</li>
      <li><strong>Device settings:</strong> mobile devices typically provide cookie controls in their privacy settings.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">
      Please note that blocking essential cookies may prevent you from using key features of X-ROR,
      such as logging in.
    </p>

    <!-- 5. More Information -->
    <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-bold">5. More Information</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">
      For more details about how we handle your personal data, see our
      <%= link_to "Privacy Policy", privacy_path %>. If you have questions about our use of cookies,
      contact us at
      <a href="mailto:[PRIVACY_EMAIL]" class="underline hover:text-foreground">[PRIVACY_EMAIL]</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</main>
